{"type":"text","timestamp":1780926618894,"sessionID":"ses_1588409bdffe2CliO0RAdlpPIC","part":{"id":"prt_ea77e69b700173wtKwgYfcQhe6","messageID":"msg_ea77d0e30001k4JZQMi0QRk7oV","sessionID":"ses_1588409bdffe2CliO0RAdlpPIC","type":"text","text":"## 1. Per-Subsystem Comparison Table\n\n| Subsystem | What OpenLTM does distinctive | system-spec-kit equivalent today | The delta / gap | Net verdict |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Hybrid recall + scoring + explainability | FTS5 lexical candidate set first, semantic fallback when results `< limit`, then post-hoc explainer; actual sort is `decay_score`, not explainer score (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:425`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:444`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:545`, `packages/openltm-core/src/recall/explainer.ts:57`). | Stronger fused vector/BM25/FTS/graph/trigger search with FSRS and `includeTrace`. | Need actual-ranker `why_ranked`; possible semantic rescue for trigger/lexical deficits. | ADAPT explainability/rescue; REJECT OpenLTM score formula. |\n| Importance-weighted decay | Materialized `decay_score`, fixed half-life tiers, confidence multiplier, soft deprecation/archive (`migrations/011_add_decay_score_and_archive.sql:4`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/decay.ts:17`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/decay.ts:31`). | FSRS decay, HOT/WARM/COLD states, importance tiers, validation and co-activation. | Optional cached `effective_retrievability`; confidence-aware demotion; archive snapshots. | ADAPT cache/audit ideas; REJECT fixed half-lives. |\n| Janitor maintenance | Sequential embed/decay/archive/promote/dedup pass with counters, WAL/ANALYZE, pending promotion and dedup proposals (`packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/index.ts:75`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/index.ts:130`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/promote.ts:89`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/dedup.ts:211`). | Self-maintaining incremental index, embedding reconcile, health, retention sweep. | Low-frequency maintenance report; proposal queue for mined memories and dedup. | ADOPT proposal staging; ADAPT reporting; DEFER cron complexity. |\n| Lifecycle hooks + injection envelope | Session hooks with bounded startup injection, PreCompact markdown snapshot, transcript/git extraction to proposals or learned facts (`hooks/src/SessionStart.ts:17`, `packages/openltm-core/src/context.ts:30`, `hooks/src/PreCompact.ts:56`, `hooks/src/EvaluateSession.ts:223`). | Session bootstrap/resume, continuity ladder, hook cache, memory save. | Durable fallback snapshot; fixed emergency line budgets; proposal-based transcript/git learning. | ADAPT. |\n| Typed graph + conflict detection | Six relation types, BFS over incoming/outgoing edges, conflict/reinforcement buckets, compact “verify before applying” warnings (`packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:95`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:39`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:235`). | Causal edges, `contradicts`/`supersedes`, causal traversal and boosts. | Present contradictions/supersession inline during retrieval; couple suppression to verified record state. | ADAPT. |\n| Secret redaction before write | Ordered secret regex scrubber runs before learn dedup, insert, markdown export, embeddings and relations; typed markers; fail-open weakness (`packages/openltm-core/src/secretsScrubber.ts:17`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:307`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:352`, `packages/openltm-core/src/secretsScrubber.ts:100`). | Extraction redaction exists, but direct spec-doc save/indexing can persist content into SQLite/vector stores. | Pre-index scrubber across save/index paths, before content hash and embeddings. | ADOPT scrubber; REJECT fail-open/content-only scope. |\n| Provenance + audit chain | Separate provenance chain plus mutation audit with slim before/after snapshots; optional batch provenance on recall; audit survives deletion (`migrations/008_add_memory_provenance.sql:1`, `migrations/009_add_memory_audit.sql:1`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:15`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:563`). | Governed provenance fields, mutation/history surfaces, retention audit. | Controlled source-kind taxonomy, on-demand batch provenance, deletion tombstones. | ADAPT; REJECT fail-open audit. |\n| Embedding abstraction + degradation | Small provider contract with `disabled`, graceful FTS-only behavior, split embedding metadata table, rebuildable sqlite-vec index (`packages/openltm-core/src/providers/embeddingProvider.ts:17`, `packages/openltm-core/src/providers/disabled.ts:12`, `migrations/010_memory_embeddings_split.sql:5`, `packages/openltm-core/src/vec/index.ts:108`). | Fixed local ollama-nomic-768d vector shard, embedder health, reconcile. | Explicit degraded embedder state and model/dim/status metadata tied to active vector shard. | ADAPT; do not proliferate providers. |\n| Schema/DB migration discipline | Root schema plus numbered SQL migrations, checksums, baseline sentinel, explicit FTS rebuild migration (`packages/openltm-core/src/migrations.ts:44`, `packages/openltm-core/src/migrations.ts:72`, `migrations/001_baseline.sql:1`, `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:7`). | Inline schema/migration ladder, self-maintained FTS/vector surfaces. | File-backed migration history, checksums, explicit FTS rebuilds, index+vector pair backups. | ADAPT. |\n| `learn()` idempotency + cross-plugin contract | Tiny normalized-key learn/reinforce contract, embedding queue, write queue, adapter actors, roadmap for versioned plugin API (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:321`, `packages/openltm-core/src/lib/writeQueue.ts:7`, `packages/adapter-opencode/src/tools.ts:50`, `docs/internal/ROADMAP.md:147`). | Broad `memory_save`, validation, 37-tool MCP surface, governed fields. | Narrow atomic `learn/reinforce` API with capability discovery and required actor/provenance. | ADAPT/ADOPT; REJECT unscoped text-key dedupe. |\n\n## 2. Ranked Transferable Teachings\n\n| Rank | Teaching | Evidence | Target system-spec-kit surface | Verdict | Risk | Confidence | Rationale |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 1 | Add actual-pipeline `why_ranked`, not display-only scoring. | `packages/openltm-core/src/recall/explainer.ts:5`, `packages/openltm-core/src/recall/explainer.ts:57`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:545`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:570` | `memory_search(includeTrace)`, `memory_context(profile=debug)` | ADAPT | LOW | 0.94 | FSRS/causal/trigger scoring is stronger than OpenLTM’s formula, but users still need a compact per-result explanation derived from the actual fused ranker. |\n| 2 | Scrub secrets before indexing, hashing, embeddings, FTS and persistence. | `packages/openltm-core/src/secretsScrubber.ts:17`, `packages/openltm-core/src/secretsScrubber.ts:21`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:307`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:314`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:352` | `memory_save`, `memory_index_scan`, embedding and FTS mutation paths | ADOPT | MED | 0.88 | FSRS and causal edges do nothing once a secret is embedded or written into SQLite/vector caches; write-path redaction is a genuine safety gap. |\n| 3 | Stage auto-mined memories and dedup as proposals, never silent durable mutation. | `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/promote.ts:51`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/promote.ts:89`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/dedup.ts:211`, `hooks/lib/proposalQueue.ts:14` | Shadow feedback reducers, proposed-memory review queue, dedup queue | ADOPT | MED | 0.88 | Self-maintaining indexing keeps data fresh, but it does not protect quality or causal lineage from bad transcript extraction or destructive duplicate merges. |\n| 4 | Surface contradiction and supersession warnings inline with retrieval. | `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:235`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:239`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:682`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:50` | `memory_search`, `memory_context`, response formatter | ADAPT | MED | 0.84 | system-spec-kit already has causal edges; the delta is putting `contradicts`/`supersedes` warnings where agents consume memories, not only in graph-debug tools. |\n| 5 | Publish a narrow atomic `learn/reinforce` contract with capability discovery. | `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:321`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:347`, `packages/openltm-core/src/lib/writeQueue.ts:13`, `docs/internal/ROADMAP.md:147`, `docs/internal/ROADMAP.md:151` | New small write/read MCP contract beside `memory_save` | ADAPT | MED | 0.87 | The 37-tool surface is powerful but too broad for cross-tool fact writes; a small actor/provenance-aware contract gives reinforcement without bypassing governance. |\n| 6 | Normalize provenance source-kind and expose provenance by batch lookup on demand. | `migrations/008_add_memory_provenance.sql:9`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:377`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:563`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:89` | `memory_index`, `memory_save`, `memory_search(includeTrace)` | ADAPT | LOW | 0.90 | Existing governed provenance strings are useful, but a controlled source-kind makes scan, import, promotion and janitor origins machine-auditable. |\n| 7 | Keep audit snapshots slim and make deletion lineage survive cleanup. | `migrations/009_add_memory_audit.sql:1`, `migrations/009_add_memory_audit.sql:6`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:15`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:18` | Mutation ledger, `memory_delete`, `memory_bulk_delete`, retention sweep | ADAPT | LOW-MED | 0.88 | Separate vector stores make full snapshots expensive; slim text/metadata tombstones improve debuggability without replacing FSRS or causal lineage. |\n| 8 | Make vector availability/degradation explicit and traceable. | `packages/openltm-core/src/providers/embeddingProvider.ts:17`, `packages/openltm-core/src/providers/disabled.ts:12`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:444`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:457` | `embedder_list`, `memory_health`, `memory_search` trace | ADAPT | LOW | 0.90 | system-spec-kit has a fixed local vector model, but local Ollama and shard coverage can still fail; explicit degraded states prevent silent lexical-only behavior. |\n| 9 | Treat vector/ANN indexes as rebuildable derived surfaces keyed by model/dim. | `migrations/010_memory_embeddings_split.sql:5`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/embeddings.ts:35`, `packages/openltm-core/src/vec/index.ts:108`, `packages/openltm-core/src/vec/index.ts:119` | Active vector shard metadata, `memory_embedding_reconcile`, embedder status | ADOPT | LOW | 0.88 | The current separate vector topology is better than OpenLTM’s same-file split, but model/dim/status metadata would make reconciliation and shard activation safer. |\n| 10 | Move future DB changes toward numbered migrations with checksums and a baseline sentinel. | `packages/openltm-core/src/migrations.ts:44`, `packages/openltm-core/src/migrations.ts:72`, `packages/openltm-core/src/migrations.ts:239`, `migrations/001_baseline.sql:1` | SQLite schema runner, migration history, release discipline | ADAPT | MED | 0.90 | Self-maintaining indexes do not solve schema drift; file-backed migration history improves auditability while preserving the existing compatibility gate. |\n| 11 | Make FTS rebuilds explicit migrations that repopulate source tables and recreate triggers. | `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:127`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:132`, `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:7`, `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:17`, `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:24` | FTS5 schema maintenance and `memory_health` repair reporting | ADAPT | MED | 0.82 | Trigger and lexical search are already present, but explicit rebuild migrations reduce hidden drift in a hybrid semantic+lexical store. |\n| 12 | Add bounded emergency context envelopes and a low-tech PreCompact snapshot. | `hooks/src/SessionStart.ts:17`, `hooks/src/SessionStart.ts:20`, `packages/openltm-core/src/context.ts:30`, `packages/openltm-core/src/context.ts:39`, `hooks/src/PreCompact.ts:56` | Session bootstrap/resume, compaction hook, continuity ladder | ADAPT | LOW | 0.87 | The spec-folder ladder is richer, but fixed quotas plus an omitted-count snapshot are easier to trust under compaction or hook-cache loss. |\n| 13 | Use lexical/trigger deficit detection to trigger semantic rescue. | `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:444`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:448`, `packages/openltm-core/src/embeddings.ts:261`, `packages/openltm-core/src/embeddings.ts:301` | `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_quick_search`, retrieval fallback policy | ADAPT | MED | 0.87 | Full `memory_search` is already fused, but trigger-first paths can still miss paraphrases; deficit rescue patches that gap without replacing triggers. |\n| 14 | Add maintenance observability, not a heavyweight janitor. | `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/index.ts:51`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/index.ts:130`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/index.ts:139`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/archive.ts:49` | `memory_health`, `memory_index_scan`, `memory_embedding_reconcile`, retention sweep | ADAPT | LOW | 0.88 | Self-maintaining incremental indexing remains the right core, but last-run counters, stale-candidate reports and per-memory archive snapshots improve operator trust. |\n\n## 3. Cross-Cutting Themes\n\n| Theme | Synthesis |\n| --- | --- |\n| Propose, do not mutate | OpenLTM’s strongest transferable pattern is staging uncertain promotion, transcript extraction, git learning, relation inference and dedup as proposals. system-spec-kit should keep shadow-first reducers and extend them to memory admission and duplicate handling. |\n| Explain every retrieval path | The recurring gap is not retrieval power. It is observability: actual-ranker contribution, channel availability, provenance source, and contradiction/supersession warnings should be visible when requested. |\n| Write-path safety beats retrieval cleverness | Redaction, provenance, actor requirements, atomic idempotency and deletion tombstones matter before FSRS, causal edges or co-activation can help. Bad writes become durable bad memory. |\n| Derived surfaces must be rebuildable and auditable | FTS, vector shards, retrievability caches and migrations should be treated as derived or versioned surfaces with checksums, model/dim metadata, repair reports and pair-aware backups. |\n\n## 4. Consolidated Negative Knowledge\n\n| Do not copy | Reason | Evidence |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| OpenLTM’s FTS-primary recall architecture wholesale | It is simpler candidate generation, not better than system-spec-kit’s fused vector/BM25/FTS/graph/trigger search. | `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:425`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:444` |\n| Display-only blended ranking scores | OpenLTM explains with one formula but sorts by `decay_score`; copying that would corrupt feedback interpretation. | `packages/openltm-core/src/recall/explainer.ts:57`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:545` |\n| Fixed importance half-lives as the relevance model | FSRS and co-activation are more adaptive than 14/30/90/180-day buckets. | `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/decay.ts:20`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/decay.ts:26` |\n| Hard `confirm_count` immortality | Repeated confirmations should feed FSRS/validation strength, not make stale facts permanent. | `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:246`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:258` |\n| Fail-open secret scrubbing or audit writes | Persisting original text on scrubber failure or losing audit silently is unacceptable for canonical memory writes. | `packages/openltm-core/src/secretsScrubber.ts:100`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:132` |\n| Content-only redaction | Titles, provenance, trigger phrases and summaries can also carry secrets. | `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:350`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:382` |\n| Direct git-diff auto-learn into durable memory | Commit diffs are noisy; route to proposals with provenance review. | `hooks/src/GitCommit.ts:117`, `hooks/src/GitCommit.ts:132`, `hooks/lib/llmExtract.ts:53` |\n| Flat goal/progress/decision/gotcha storage as a replacement for spec folders | system-spec-kit’s continuity ladder, causal edges and tiers are richer and more auditable. | `packages/openltm-core/src/context.ts:16`, `packages/openltm-core/src/context.ts:44` |\n| `relate()` semantics as-is | `INSERT OR IGNORE` cannot update edge metadata and `supersedes` does not change record state. | `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:587`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:603` |\n| Unused edge weights or graph UI machinery | Metadata not consumed by traversal/scoring is dead surface; layout/cluster UI does not improve continuity recall. | `migrations/018_relation_semantics.sql:2`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:51`, `src/cluster.ts:8` |\n| Provider proliferation | system-spec-kit should keep local ollama-nomic and improve degraded-state reporting, not chase many provider integrations. | `packages/openltm-core/src/providers/embeddingProvider.ts:7`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/providers/types.ts:149` |\n| Schema/docs drift patterns | Split `_schema_version` vs `schema_migrations`, commented-only downs, stale embedding columns and unwired knobs all show the cost of unsynchronized contracts. | `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:5`, `packages/openltm-core/src/migrations.ts:25`, `migrations/010_memory_embeddings_split.sql:25`, `packages/openltm-core/src/config.ts:17` |\n| Single-file DB backup assumptions | system-spec-kit’s index DB and active vector shard must be checkpointed as a pair. | `packages/openltm-core/src/migrations.ts:76`, `packages/openltm-core/src/migrations.ts:231` |\n| 200-char normalized text dedupe | It can over-merge across folders, categories or actors; use scoped hashes/atomic upsert instead. | `packages/openltm-core/src/dedup.ts:5`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dedup.ts:6`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:45` |\n| Exposing the whole MCP/admin surface as cross-plugin contract | Other tools need a small versioned read/write subset with actor/provenance requirements. | `docs/internal/ROADMAP.md:147`, `docs/internal/ROADMAP.md:151`, `packages/adapter-opencode/src/tools.ts:30` |","time":{"start":1780926540215,"end":1780926618887},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c9035790e82e66f016a26c84c2c20819192f08362f87e9bc9","phase":"final_answer"}}}}
